text: Eindhoven University of Technology (Dutch: Technische Universiteit Eindhoven), shortened to TU/e, is a technical public university in Eindhoven, a city in the province of North Brabant, the Netherlands. Eindhoven University of Technology was established in 1956. It has about 11,000 students. Its focus is on technology. == Other websites == * Category:1956 establishments in the Netherlands Category:Eindhoven Category:Technical colleges and universities in the Netherlands
